                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zarath wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I really didn't come here to troll, I came here to give the counterpoint that you guys were missing, to give the rationale behind that of a DPS class and why we might be upset about it. But in true bitter player fashion (and I am a Mage, I know bitter) it's easier at first to label those that have opposing view points trolls. It helps to ease the pain.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
The last thing we need is "counterpoint" from a magician who doesn't understand the issues.
<br />

<br />
No offense, but concentrate on fixing your own damn class.  You have your own fish to fry.  For some reason, mages seem content to cry nerf or support nerfs on every other class in some misguided attempt to balance the rest of these classes with themselves.
<br />

<br />
Nerf beastlords -- their pets are as good or better than ours, plus they can slow and heal their pets better than we can.  Nerf necros -- they have so much more utility than we do, have better defense and escape mechanisms than we do, do more damage than we do.  Nerf wizards -- they outdamage us with their superior nukes.  Nerf rogues -- they outdamage us with their backstabs and superior weaponry.  Nerf druids -- our nukes are only as good as theirs, but they can dire charm pets and heal groups.
<br />

<br />
I go to the mage boards, and that's what I read so it really doesn't surprise me to see mages applaud the charm nerf as vigorously as they do.  Nerf enchanters -- their charmed pets do more DPS than our pets do, even the dire charm pets.
<br />

<br />
A few of the mages actually try to do positive things to improve their class, but even some of those attempts are heavily marred by class envy.  Fix your own class.  Lobby for improved pet damage -- unless you're seriously satisfied with PoP and Omens pet damage, which I somehow doubt.  Lobby for improved nukes.  Lobby for better self-defense and escape mechanisms.  Fix your own damn class.  Then come back to us and provide "counterpoint" if you wish.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
<br />
