I'll ignore the personal attacks and vitriol of your post for a moment and focus on this.
<br />

<br />
Look at our top 10. Look at about any mage complaint, it's pet damage. We have been lacking since Kunark (barring the once a year epic). We are trying desperately to get our class fixed. However you all know how bad Sony is with fixing mistakes and how frustrating silence is. 
<br />

<br />
So, for a moment pretend that you are a Mage. You campaign for the pets you need to fulfill your class description, and Sony still refuses to see that their method of scaling is flawed from the baseline, and pets lose comparative power as you get farther into the high end. Your class has sacrificed all defense and most utility for the damage you do and the pets you have. Sony still is silent. They, however, give upgrades to other classes that violate the rules they themselves put forward, ie giving DPS without taking utility. Mages have little utility and still lackluster pets.
<br />

<br />
Now, reread most of the Mage posts on the Tower about balance. Very few actually call for nerfs, and those that do are usually shot down. (Charm, granted, being the exception because not only Mages saw how overpowering that ammount of damage was) Most of the posts that even deal with other classes use them as a comparison for relative power and ask for Mage upgrades, such as the hypothetical "Our pets should do double the damage of Shaman dogs."
<br />

<br />
So to call all Mages whiners (when we are just doing what you yourself have agreed that we should do) or nerfers (when nerf calling is just as looked down upon there as it is here) is myopic and bigoted in the least.
