                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes, you soloed two low blue mobs in seventeen minutes, thus the charm nerf must be perfect. I could solo those with a dot too, does that mean I should be casting our dots in groups? I could solo those by tanking and letting the animation kill it, should I do that in groups?
<br />

<br />
The problem is, the previous nerfs to charm made it a big pain in the ass. Exp loss. Four man rule. Bad breaks. The balance before was the reward of having a powerful pet. 
<br />

<br />
Now, we have all the downside, and very little upside. Can you still solo in a gimped way? Of course. Would you be in that zone at all if it was not for the rune drops? Of course you wouldn't. The experience sucks, even solo. The loot sucks, other than the runes. Basically, you are using charm to farm stuff. 
<br />

<br />
Soloing in that instance is a very contrived kind of thing. Go solo in a zone like WoS and I will be a bit more impressed. (I picked WoS as it seems to be a zone where people experience, and also has mobs low enough to charm with CoD)
<br />

<br />
And frankly, soloing is sometimes easier than grouping with charm. Easier to stay alive, anyhow. When charm breaks, and you have three mobs in camp, and you are lom, and you are soloing? Gee, I just gate, med up, and go back in. If I have a group, I have to deal with things more. I certainly die more charming in groups than soloing.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
