                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sorry for the off-topic but I gotta ask:
<br />

<br />
NoprobsEMarr - Are you taking a level- appropriate DZ to solo? I know I have tried both a 65 and 68+ version, and the 68+ that is intended for me is not really feasible - certainly not worth the risk/effort unless I want to be stubborn to prove a point.
<br />

<br />
But the 65 DZ is doable - because all my spells actually work there and arent nerfed, besides charm which operates at 50% there though and not the much lower percentages higher mobs have. So I'm good against content that I'm "too high" for, and probably "over-equipped" too. Taken to the extreme "we're fine because we can solo blackburrow" - I dont think so.
<br />

<br />
Even with nerfed charm - playing around in the "lowbie" 65 DZ and the DZ targeted at lvl70s clearly shows how much we've lost with OoW.
<br />

<br />
And on topic (i think) - the loss of our crowd control abilities is one of the factors why the risk/reward of charmed is way off now. Charmed pet dps being low would be much more acceptable if my other spells allowed me to deal with my pet alone - but they dont. Our defensive spells are removed/nerfed, our defensive AA are all on reuse timers too long to be readily available and are too weak in general. So charm dps still requires group effort, just now for half a rogue's dps. No group lets you feed *their* xp to a charmed pet under these conditions.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7110" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jennifer DeGartes</a>, Enchantress of <a href="http://www.vazaelle.dk" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caer Cadarn</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
