                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Jenn,
<br />
No, I used a lvl 66 to get the instance for me. Not tried the 68+ one to be honest, so I get your point there. Mine was, for little risk I got good rewards.
<br />
___
<br />

<br />
Someone else asked if I had tried to solo in WoS yet. Not yet, but I might try. Then again, I don't really see anyone soloing in WoS. So what's your point? Encs should be able to solo where no other classes do? When it comes to soloing for xp wiz/nec/dru/shm have had us beat even before our charms were originally nerfed. Eg Table camp in the 2nd castle of fire. I don't see any Nec/Wiz/Dru/Shm soloing in WoS and so I wouldn't even expect to as an Enc.
<br />

<br />
I just don't see charm being nerfed/fixed/balanced/unbalanced or whatever as being so huge a deal, we're still a pretty handy class to have in your group in tight situations.
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't mind seeing an improved resist adj. to our mezzes, mobs that take 5secs to give you a free TL to bind are no fun on a mez resist but I don't consider our mezzes 'broken' either. I chain pull and set up my group's kills with mezzes, slows and blurs, noprobs. Let the fake pullers do what they're supposed to do, dps or singing or firing their bow and arrows or something.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Don't get me wrong though, I'd love to have my 1200 hitting Pooka back, I just can't see it happening, and in truth we and SoE should have seen this coming a long time ago.
<br />

